Comment: 10,0:02:06.80,0:02:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, protests are continuing to escalate. {probably best}
Comment: 10,0:02:10.44,0:02:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposing faction has ended their silence\Nand launched counter-protests in turn.{## my dictionaries say this is one word for some reason}{safest}
Comment: 10,0:02:14.46,0:02:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Some supporters have started\Nresorting to extreme measures.
Comment: 10,0:02:18.39,0:02:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The two countries have been at war\Nthree times since the middle ages,
Comment: 10,0:02:22.75,0:02:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and some are saying this uproar\Nmay be the start of a fourth—{## nicely timed line}
Comment: 10,0:02:29.08,0:02:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Our appeasement policy is reaching the end of its life.
Comment: 10,0:02:32.22,0:02:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They are taking us as weak-willed. This is not just a matter of winning or losing a match anymore.{## it's matches for football (soccer); "soft" can be replaced again}{literally never heard 'for soft' before}
Comment: 10,0:02:39.66,0:02:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Their whole nation thinks they can take advantage of us.{## play us for fools?}
Comment: 10,0:02:42.63,0:02:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The time for compromise is over. We must demonstrate our firm resolve!{## this dude seems to be a bit more belligerent}{might, if not for the words he uses}
Comment: 10,0:02:47.32,0:02:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really so?
Comment: 10,0:02:49.64,0:02:55.35,Default,,15,15,0,,Much time and effort was spent mending our relations.\NShould we truly be willing to let that go to waste?
Comment: 10,0:02:55.35,0:02:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What, you think you can mouth off to me again?
Comment: 10,0:02:59.42,0:03:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Andrew.
Comment: 10,0:03:01.41,0:03:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is one issue you cannot stick your nose in.
Comment: 10,0:03:04.81,0:03:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You should listen to your father's orders.
Comment: 10,0:03:08.20,0:03:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I overlooked the incident with the witch\Nat Appleton in deference to your father,
Comment: 10,0:03:13.38,0:03:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but cause any more problems,\Nand I will be forced to act.
Comment: 10,0:03:19.93,0:03:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not allow any defiance.
Comment: 10,0:03:25.67,0:03:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as I must keep cleaning up your messes, you are still a child. {for the record, this term means "wiping one's ass"}
Comment: 10,0:03:29.82,0:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is your duty and responsibility, as the Hanbridge heir, to become a great statesman.{## "line" is only really used for monarchs and assorted royalty; the hanbridge stuff is less about sitting on some throne in their shire and more about their political legacy too}
Comment: 10,0:03:36.08,0:03:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear that in mind henceforth.
Comment: 10,0:03:42.79,0:03:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't even give one word in response.{## unless this is going too far}
Comment: 10,0:03:47.69,0:03:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If she had been watching, I'd be getting called a coward about now.
Comment: 10,0:03:53.57,0:03:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's Diana's messenger.
Comment: 10,0:03:55.57,0:03:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'll be able to contact Miss Kagari.
Comment: 10,0:04:03.12,0:04:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming.
Comment: 10,0:04:06.96,0:04:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Diana?
Comment: 10,0:04:08.68,0:04:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Good day. Is Akko available? {##}
Comment: 10,0:04:11.55,0:04:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Diana's looking for Akko? She must be plotting something.
Comment: 10,0:04:15.70,0:04:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Sucy!
Comment: 10,0:04:17.17,0:04:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Akko just left to go see Professor Ursula.
Comment: 10,0:04:20.33,0:04:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Ursula?
Comment: 10,0:04:23.72,0:04:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness, you really do seem fine now.
Comment: 10,0:04:26.56,0:04:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you that there was no need to worry?
Comment: 10,0:04:30.31,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was almost fully healed back then.{## at the point when she said it i guess, or just "back then" during the incident, doesn't matter too much i'd say}{due to the sixth Word magic}
Comment: 10,0:04:32.36,0:04:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was my fault you even\Ngot hurt in the first place.
Comment: 10,0:04:35.71,0:04:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Akko, didn't you promise not to say that anymore?
Comment: 10,0:04:40.75,0:04:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Comment: 10,0:04:41.62,0:04:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad you came.
Comment: 10,0:04:44.18,0:04:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I needed to talk to you about.
Comment: 10,0:04:46.47,0:04:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Comment: 10,0:04:51.18,0:04:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I will tell you the seventh and final Word.
Comment: 10,0:04:58.05,0:05:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Phasansheer Shearylla. {fasanshi-ru sheari-ra}{## was thinking of making it similar to arae arhyrha but shearhyrha looked a bit too needlessly tough}
Comment: 10,0:05:01.66,0:05:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Phasansheer Shearylla?
Comment: 10,0:05:05.28,0:05:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even I know its meaning.
Comment: 10,0:05:08.02,0:05:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't?
Comment: 10,0:05:09.11,0:05:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember that the final Word
Comment: 10,0:05:13.99,0:05:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,lies within your heart.
Comment: 10,0:05:16.37,0:05:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Within my heart...
Comment: 10,0:05:21.49,0:05:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fax-0.2}The seventh star will shine in response to the feelings in your heart. {the critical difference here is that in this version, there's still that non-determinism, as in it's not guaranteed. "as it answers to" sounds more like it will definitely happen}
Comment: 10,0:05:30.93,0:05:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When the seventh star shines, say the final Word.
Comment: 10,0:05:37.32,0:05:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Comment: 10,0:05:41.67,0:05:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one more thing I need to tell you.
Comment: 10,0:05:43.97,0:05:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? There is?
Comment: 10,0:05:53.68,0:05:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I've been trying to find\Nthe right time to tell you for so long.
Comment: 10,0:05:59.22,0:06:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, the truth is—
Comment: 10,0:06:00.47,0:06:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Akko here?
Comment: 10,0:06:01.63,0:06:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Comment: 10,0:06:03.93,0:06:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! Diana too?
Comment: 10,0:06:05.75,0:06:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a message from Andrew.
Comment: 10,0:06:08.02,0:06:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be waiting for you at High Street today.
Comment: 10,0:06:10.79,0:06:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, Andrew said that? Today?
Comment: 10,0:06:13.31,0:06:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got something to give you.
Comment: 10,0:06:15.67,0:06:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? But, today...
Comment: 10,0:06:18.42,0:06:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What time today?
Comment: 10,0:06:19.73,0:06:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At three o—
Comment: 10,0:06:20.80,0:06:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Three?!
Comment: 10,0:06:22.86,0:06:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cutting it close.
Comment: 10,0:06:24.31,0:06:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Comment: 10,0:06:25.20,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead. We can continue our conversation after you get back.
Comment: 10,0:06:28.70,0:06:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Professor! I'll be right back!
Comment: 10,0:06:30.94,0:06:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Lotte, but could you give me a ride? {## i hunger for commas}
Comment: 10,0:06:32.91,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, let's hurry.
Comment: 10,0:06:34.04,0:06:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse us!
Comment: 10,0:06:39.48,0:06:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's unusual for you to come here.
Comment: 10,0:06:43.26,0:06:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something I would like to ask you.
Comment: 10,0:06:45.91,0:06:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a question for {\fax-0.2}me{\i0}?
Comment: 10,0:06:47.36,0:06:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hopefully I'll be able to answer it for you...
Comment: 10,0:06:51.47,0:06:56.88,Default,,15,15,0,,Are you aware of the recent concentration of magic energy,\Nsurpassing even the output of the Sorcerer's Stone?
Comment: 10,0:06:56.88,0:07:05.26,Default,,15,15,0,,After looking into it, events relating to that matter began after Professor Croix installed her SSS in Luna Nova.
Comment: 10,0:07:05.59,0:07:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you were old friends with Professor Croix, so I had hoped you might know something about this.
Comment: 10,0:07:15.16,0:07:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but something just came up.
Comment: 10,0:07:21.15,0:07:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor?
Comment: 10,0:07:22.07,0:07:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll finish this later!
Comment: 10,0:07:23.78,0:07:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Comment: 10,0:07:26.37,0:07:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Comment: 10,0:07:27.58,0:07:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Was she affected by Wagandea's pollen?{## should work with the ellipses and starting a new line mid-sentence? i think it's best to split the line in any case. if it doesn't work, the original line is just fine}
Comment: 10,0:07:35.42,0:07:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, out of everyone it could've been,\NI never expected you to call for me.{## still not quite bikkuri but a bit closer + referring to the disrupted talk with ursula}
Comment: 10,0:07:39.03,0:07:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, but I wanted to return this.
Comment: 10,0:07:41.88,0:07:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. I forgot it in your car back then.
Comment: 10,0:07:45.54,0:07:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I intended to alert you immediately, but who'd\Nexpect all calls and emails to be barred?
Comment: 10,0:07:50.42,0:07:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling me.
Comment: 10,0:07:52.05,0:07:57.11,Default,,15,15,0,,All we've got is one-way messaging through magic. \NI guess that explains why you contacted Diana.
Comment: 10,0:07:57.13,0:07:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to our families.{## had "via our families" but boy did it look weird}
Comment: 10,0:07:58.27,0:08:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously though, that was way too little notice. I barely made it in time.
Comment: 10,0:08:02.33,0:08:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know I can't ride a broom?
Comment: 10,0:08:04.95,0:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you sound so proud about that?
Comment: 10,0:08:08.14,0:08:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I apologize for rushing you.\NI was on the way to Parliament with my father.{## this is one of those lines that could probably get away with a semicolon for extra sophisticated speech}
Comment: 10,0:08:13.14,0:08:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured this timing would work for us both. {I take that back, the "so" flows poorly}
Comment: 10,0:08:15.33,0:08:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Parliament? Wow, that sounds kinda fancy.
Comment: 10,0:08:18.04,0:08:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't, really. I'm just accompanying my father.
Comment: 10,0:08:22.05,0:08:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fad(2200,0)}No goal! No goal! No goal! No goal!
Comment: 10,0:08:26.22,0:08:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's that?
Comment: 10,0:08:27.64,0:08:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's actually part of the reason\Nwe're heading to Parliament.
Comment: 10,0:08:31.06,0:08:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Comment: 10,0:08:32.10,0:08:37.87,Default,,15,15,0,,The enmity from a soccer match escalated and ended up\N{ gravely} exacerbating the hatred between our nation and theirs.{## need this for the next line}
Comment: 10,0:08:37.87,0:08:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There seem to be similar demonstrations within their borders too. {demonstration is correct}
Comment: 10,0:08:40.92,0:08:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our two countries have been at ends since the Middle Ages.{## shouganai wa ne}
Comment: 10,0:08:44.53,0:08:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Only recently were things finally starting to improve.{## too tired to wrap my head around this phrasing tbh}
Comment: 10,0:08:48.98,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet look how little it took \Nto set{## or "put"} us back on edge again.
Comment: 10,0:08:53.33,0:08:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's such a shame.
Comment: 10,0:08:57.64,0:09:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what their reasons are, I just can't understand how they can keep being so angry. {the world needs Akko}
Comment: 10,0:09:03.29,0:09:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And... it kind of scares me too.
Comment: 10,0:09:06.47,0:09:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm with you.
Comment: 10,0:09:09.70,0:09:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exactly the kind of situation we need Chariot for.
Comment: 10,0:09:13.27,0:09:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone should go and see Chariot's show.
Comment: 10,0:09:15.98,0:09:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd be thrilled and laugh and get emotional—{## "they'll" or "they'd", since there are no shows on at this point? more of a principle thing there; i suggest "they'd" and all edits according to that in the surrounding lines}
Comment: 10,0:09:19.18,0:09:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then all their anger and negativity will be blown away.
Comment: 10,0:09:24.82,0:09:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd laugh?
Comment: 10,0:09:25.87,0:09:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And get emotional!
Comment: 10,0:09:27.99,0:09:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, all the world will be at peace!
Comment: 10,0:09:31.97,0:09:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite the quixotic idealism.{## man it's like... it's a good fit and a good translation (IMHO), but i realize so many people will think this phrase sucks; dunno; maybe use "improbable" or just the initial line}
Comment: 10,0:09:34.08,0:09:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Comment: 10,0:09:35.49,0:09:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not laughing? Usually, you'd be\Nsnorting at me or something.
Comment: 10,0:09:39.98,0:09:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't laugh.
Comment: 10,0:09:40.96,0:09:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be wonderful if that could turn into reality.
Comment: 10,0:09:44.26,0:09:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Far better than what's happening right now.
Comment: 10,0:09:47.82,0:09:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You've come to accept magic just a little bit more than before.
Comment: 10,0:09:53.78,0:09:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps my opinion of you has improved slightly over time.
Comment: 10,0:09:57.76,0:09:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's one thing I must say.
Comment: 10,0:09:59.31,0:10:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You want people to be moved and happiness brought upon them.
Comment: 10,0:10:02.89,0:10:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's the point if you just rely on Chariot and don't do it yourself?
Comment: 10,0:10:06.53,0:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You mean {\fax-0.2}I{\i0} should do it?
Comment: 10,0:10:08.06,0:10:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you disagree?
Comment: 10,0:10:10.90,0:10:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you've got it right.
Comment: 10,0:10:13.35,0:10:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll do it!
Comment: 10,0:10:14.99,0:10:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Comment: 10,0:10:15.70,0:10:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that look? You can bet I'll do it!
Comment: 10,0:10:18.83,0:10:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch me, Andrew!
Comment: 10,0:10:39.48,0:10:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That thing!
Comment: 10,0:10:45.15,0:10:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it before!
Comment: 10,0:10:47.52,0:10:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Andrew! I've gotta go!
Comment: 10,0:10:49.78,0:10:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Comment: 10,0:10:50.44,0:10:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure—
Comment: 10,0:10:59.64,0:11:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point if you don't do it yourself?
Comment: 10,0:11:03.01,0:11:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Comment: 10,0:11:09.01,0:11:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if things are going well with Akko and Andrew.
Comment: 10,0:11:12.50,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back!
Comment: 10,0:11:18.83,0:11:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Comment: 10,0:11:19.97,0:11:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess not.
Comment: 10,0:11:26.49,0:11:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Akko?
Comment: 10,0:11:27.58,0:11:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You should really try to limit your foolishness to the school grounds.
Comment: 10,0:11:31.61,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Comment: 10,0:11:33.96,0:11:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That looks like the things that were flying around during the strike.
Comment: 10,0:11:37.24,0:11:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember seeing them at the Wild Hunt too.
Comment: 10,0:11:39.37,0:11:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad stuff happens whenever these things are around.
Comment: 10,0:11:46.56,0:11:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There too...
Comment: 10,0:11:47.95,0:11:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a bad feeling about this.
Comment: 10,0:12:14.21,0:12:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Comment: 10,0:12:15.17,0:12:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Comment: 10,0:12:17.17,0:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those bastards!
Comment: 10,0:12:19.17,0:12:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll pay for this!
Comment: 10,0:12:20.61,0:12:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is war!
Comment: 10,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only getting worse.
Comment: 10,0:12:33.60,0:12:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Akko?
Comment: 10,0:12:52.45,0:12:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Croix?
Comment: 10,0:13:07.05,0:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Croix!
Comment: 10,0:13:08.89,0:13:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad, Professor Croix!
Comment: 10,0:13:11.64,0:13:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Comment: 10,0:13:14.23,0:13:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, there's a very complicated reason for that...
Comment: 10,0:13:17.27,0:13:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So it was only coincidence\Nthat brought you to the city.
Comment: 10,0:13:22.14,0:13:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even have Claimh Solais on you.
Comment: 10,0:13:24.67,0:13:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Claimh Solais? What's that?
Comment: 10,0:13:29.52,0:13:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's not important right now!
Comment: 10,0:13:32.37,0:13:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw all these weird, square-y things all over town! {not cubey}
Comment: 10,0:13:35.64,0:13:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're definitely doing something bad!
Comment: 10,0:13:38.35,0:13:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like that!
Comment: 10,0:13:39.60,0:13:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that thing!
Comment: 10,0:13:45.06,0:13:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Comment: 10,0:13:48.09,0:13:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I developed these in order to convert emotions into energy.
Comment: 10,0:13:59.90,0:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You made those people...? {interestingly, this is ideal}
Comment: 10,0:14:02.40,0:14:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite.
Comment: 10,0:14:04.13,0:14:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotion of anger comes from within them.
Comment: 10,0:14:08.14,0:14:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All I did was enhance it slightly and absorb it.
Comment: 10,0:14:12.17,0:14:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Absorb it? But why?
Comment: 10,0:14:15.45,0:14:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Noir Fuel Spirit. {we had it like this but I'd say we can capitalize it}{## yeah, blame the editor. this is better}
Comment: 10,0:14:18.67,0:14:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can convert strong human emotions\Ninto powerful magic energy.
Comment: 10,0:14:23.42,0:14:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I am probing the hearts of people around the world—
Comment: 10,0:14:27.49,0:14:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H3D2183&}Anger, {\3c&H310A2A&\t(1398,1398,\3c&H893875&)}hatred, {\3c&H310A2A&\t(2774,2774,\3c&H892E4C&)}sadness, {\3c&H310A2A&\t(4026,4026,\3c&H823E25&)}jealousy, {\3c&H310A2A&\t(5110,5110,\3c&H6A7325&)}fear, {\3c&H310A2A&\t(6278,6278,\3c&H336529&)}anxiety—{## hmm... i get what you were going for, but i wonder if it really looks as good in practice as you thought it'd look like in theory. i mean, i used gimmicky subtitling tricks too so i'm not one to speak, but... yeah. maybe mute the colors a bit more even if they don't perfectly fit the cube colors anymore}{done}{improved}
Comment: 10,0:14:34.73,0:14:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to completely absorb all of those emotions.
Comment: 10,0:14:39.02,0:14:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Absorb... emotions?
Comment: 10,0:14:42.27,0:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be aware as well.
Comment: 10,0:14:44.80,0:14:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic is in decline all around the world.
Comment: 10,0:14:47.98,0:14:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If nothing is done, magic will one day disappear entirely.
Comment: 10,0:14:51.74,0:14:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We need a method to generate it\Nfrom some sort of energy.{## maybe "create"}
Comment: 10,0:14:55.05,0:15:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see how fantastic it would be if we could harvest human emotions as a new energy source?{## one "convert" too many at this point, plus its usage was in contradiction to the previous line, or at least made the process emotions --> energy --> magic too convoluted; "that very" might be pushing it, plus line length considerations, so meh}{Croix is literally the one using the same word}
Comment: 10,0:15:02.93,0:15:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Manipulation is easiest with crowd psychology.{## okay obviously your call, but make it so it doesn't sound like she's manipulating crowd/mob psychology, which doesn't make a ton of sense, but manipulates through crowd/mob psychology}
Comment: 10,0:15:05.67,0:15:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been gathering emotions through this app...{## their emotions? those emotions? something is better than nothing}
Comment: 10,0:15:10.47,0:15:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the results far exceed my expectations!
Comment: 10,0:15:12.61,0:15:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more than enough for my world reconstruction plan to come to fruition!
Comment: 10,0:15:16.47,0:15:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll all see magic in a new light!
Comment: 10,0:15:19.22,0:15:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Croix, you're acting weird!
Comment: 10,0:15:21.77,0:15:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop doing something like that!
Comment: 10,0:15:23.65,0:15:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Are you saying you wouldn't mind\Nif magic was lost forever?
Comment: 10,0:15:28.12,0:15:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic won't go away! I won't let it! {ep 6ish}
Comment: 10,0:15:30.58,0:15:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Comment: 10,0:15:32.53,0:15:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Feelings by themselves can't change the world—you must take action.
Comment: 10,0:15:37.03,0:15:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Still... this is wrong!
Comment: 10,0:15:40.10,0:15:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic...
Comment: 10,0:15:41.10,0:15:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic should be used to make people happy!
Comment: 10,0:15:45.79,0:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You say the same things as Chariot.
Comment: 10,0:15:49.96,0:15:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is exactly why she failed.
Comment: 10,0:15:53.30,0:15:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't comprehend incompetent witches who do nothing but chase after unachievable dreams.
Comment: 10,0:15:58.55,0:16:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a waste of time.
Comment: 10,0:16:00.95,0:16:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our private lesson ends here.
Comment: 10,0:16:42.92,0:16:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay right there and keep your mouth shut.
Comment: 10,0:17:04.40,0:17:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Diphulaniado! {difurania-do}
Comment: 10,0:17:18.77,0:17:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Chariot...
Comment: 10,0:17:31.56,0:17:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor... Ursula?
Comment: 10,0:17:35.91,0:17:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never learned how to keep your head down. {lit. you incorrigibly appeared}{## no idea where to take this but i kinda don't like this line too much}{for the record, this is a stock phrase}
Comment: 10,0:17:38.36,0:17:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still intend to interfere, Chariot du Nord?
Comment: 10,0:17:42.08,0:17:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chariot?
Comment: 10,0:17:44.15,0:17:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're... Shiny Chariot?
Comment: 10,0:17:48.61,0:17:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So you {\fax-0.2}finally{\i0} realized? Didn't I say you'd meet her soon?
Comment: 10,0:17:52.53,0:17:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The person you've so admired has always been\Nright next to you, pulling the wool over your eyes.
Comment: 10,0:17:58.14,0:18:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I kept this a secret from you.
Comment: 10,0:18:01.22,0:18:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to tell you properly.
Comment: 10,0:18:04.98,0:18:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Croix!
Comment: 10,0:18:06.69,0:18:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your methods are mistaken!
Comment: 10,0:18:08.40,0:18:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you intend to stop me?
Comment: 10,0:18:11.82,0:18:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You? Stop me? I'm surprised you can\Nsay that with a straight face.
Comment: 10,0:18:16.03,0:18:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember what you did ten years ago?
Comment: 10,0:18:20.59,0:18:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you be the one to tell her what happened the day Chariot descended from the stage forever?
Comment: 10,0:18:26.16,0:18:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly it was that you did to the moon.
Comment: 10,0:18:33.66,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream Fuel Spirit.
Comment: 10,0:18:36.14,0:18:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic to convert the power of dreaming\Ninto strong magical energy.
Comment: 10,0:18:39.72,0:18:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly gives you the right to stop me after using that yourself? {now who's overusing "so"?}
Comment: 10,0:18:43.33,0:18:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That power—
Comment: 10,0:18:44.16,0:18:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Convert the power of dreaming into magic?
Comment: 10,0:18:54.65,0:18:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see how it is now.
Comment: 10,0:18:57.86,0:19:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the true reason you care so much about her.
Comment: 10,0:19:02.63,0:19:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Akko.
Comment: 10,0:19:03.99,0:19:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw Chariot's show in the past, didn't you?
Comment: 10,0:19:06.45,0:19:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Comment: 10,0:19:07.24,0:19:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream Fuel Spirit gathers the dreaming energy of everyone in the area and turns it into magic. {so apparently, the "fuel spirit" thing is more of a process than a fuel itself}{## well yeah, croix says it's a form of magic. but we could/should keep it capitalized since it's so ostensibly a loanword/weirdo english-language construction}
Comment: 10,0:19:13.42,0:19:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And those whose dreams are absorbed...
Comment: 10,0:19:16.13,0:19:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Lose their magic.
Comment: 10,0:19:22.51,0:19:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Chariot?
Comment: 10,0:19:24.38,0:19:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell her yourself.
Comment: 10,0:19:41.35,0:19:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When I learned that you once saw a Chariot show, I hoped it wasn't true.{## can't they at least fire real football hool flares, this is so lame for a mob}
Comment: 10,0:19:47.74,0:19:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe it.
Comment: 10,0:19:50.30,0:19:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But after all the time we spent together,\NI couldn't deny it anymore.
Comment: 10,0:19:55.13,0:20:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In all likelihood, I was the one who absorbed your magic.
Comment: 10,0:20:00.84,0:20:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you can't fly...
Comment: 10,0:20:03.84,0:20:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is all my fault.
Comment: 10,0:20:12.74,0:20:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie...
Comment: 10,0:20:14.06,0:20:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Professor Ursula...
Comment: 10,0:20:19.32,0:20:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Say... it's a lie...
Comment: 10,0:20:32.36,0:20:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be a lie...
Comment: 10,0:20:34.59,0:20:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie...
Comment: 10,0:20:37.85,0:20:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie...
Comment: 10,0:21:52.43,0:21:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fax-0.2}Never forget.
Comment: 10,0:21:54.71,0:21:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fax-0.2}A believing heart is your magic.
Comment: 10,0:22:04.86,0:22:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!{## this one makes me think "that's not true!" might have been an option, plus of course for all preceding lines, but eh}{I'm putting this in the same folder as Rena}
Comment: 10,0:22:11.90,0:22:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt she'll be looking for the Words any longer.
Comment: 10,0:22:15.83,0:22:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet again, you couldn't reach it.
Comment: 10,0:22:19.04,0:22:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The seventh Word.{## probably not entirely correct but we can't have "you couldn't reach it" / "to the seventh word"; also seriously, flares might've been much made for a much nicer backdrop for the final scene, and nothing will top mouryou no hako's fireworks final scene anyway}
